# CSVInspector ğŸ•µï¸â€â™‚ï¸

CSVInspector is a powerful Python library for automating preprocessing and exploratory data analysis (EDA) on CSV datasets. Itâ€™s built to help data scientists and analysts quickly understand the structure and quality of their data â€” all in one go.

---

## âœ¨ Features

- ğŸ“Œ Basic info summary (rows, columns, data types)
- ğŸ§¬ Automatic feature type detection
- ğŸš« Missing data detection and heatmaps
- ğŸ“‰ Correlation matrix + heatmap
- ğŸ“Š Distribution plots (before/after outlier removal)
- ğŸ§ª Outlier detection summary
- ğŸ”„ Skewness detection with transformation suggestions
- ğŸª„ Normalization summaries (MinMaxScaler, StandardScaler)
- ğŸ“ˆ Quantile summaries for quick statistics
- ğŸ“‹ Optional quality score
- ğŸ“„ Comprehensive Markdown report generation

---

## ğŸ“¦ Installation

```bash
pip install csvinspector
```

---

## ğŸš€ Usage

Hereâ€™s a minimal example using `CSVInspector`:

```python
from csvinspector import CSVInspector

inspector = CSVInspector("your_dataset.csv")
summary = inspector.run_analysis()
```

This will generate:
- A detailed Markdown report in `inspection_output/report.md`
- Plots and visualizations in the same folder
- A dictionary object `summary` with all analysis results

